body:
the workaround i am using is:

```toml
[custom.git_sha256]
command = "git rev-parse --abbrev-ref HEAD"
when = "git rev-parse --show-object-format 2>/dev/null | grep -q sha256"
shell = ["bash", "--noprofile", "--norc"]
format = "on [git $output]($style) "
style = "purple bold"

[custom.git_sha256_status]
command = """
_status_info="$(git status --porcelain --branch)"
echo "${_status_info}" | awk '
  NR==1 && /ahead/ {_ah=">"}
  NR==1 && /behind/ {_bh="<"}
  NR>1 && /^ [MDAU]/ {_mod="!"}
  NR>1 && /^[MDAU] / {_stg="+"}
  NR>1 && /^\\?\\?/ {_unt="?"}
  NR>1 && (/^ D/ || /^D /) {_del="x"}
  NR>1 && (/^ R/ || /^R /) {_ren="r"}
  END {
    _out = _ren _stg _mod _unt _del _ah _bh
    if (_out != "") { printf "[%s]", _out }
  }
'
"""
when = "git rev-parse --show-object-format 2>/dev/null | grep -q sha256"
shell = ["bash", "--noprofile", "--norc"]
format = "([$output]($style) )"
style = "red bold"
```

you can find my `starship.rs` config at https://github.com/akileshas/devenv.archive/blob/177db1dcaab54da19e4608b98dafd006d09bbf0f/starship/starship.toml
@e-minguez thanks for the inspiration for the workaround.
